    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2203556518" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2203556518" />
    <a title="Laszlo Makay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34852089-laszlo-makay"><img alt="Laszlo Makay" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2203556518?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laszlo Makay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laszlo Makay" href="/user/show/34852089-laszlo-makay">Laszlo Makay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2203556518" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9213576527443490590">There are various types of books around: fictions with great characters, comics with beautiful pictures and textbooks of great academic knowledge. Each has its aim and target audience. Gleb Tsipursky’s book is for those who would like to see clearly. <br/><br/>Do you feel that sometimes you are just lost among the flood of opinionated statements from businessman, religious leaders and politicians? Do you feel disoriented when targeted messages and advertisements are bombarding you from all angles? Do you </span>
  <span id="freeText9213576527443490590" style="display:none">There are various types of books around: fictions with great characters, comics with beautiful pictures and textbooks of great academic knowledge. Each has its aim and target audience. Gleb Tsipursky’s book is for those who would like to see clearly. <br /><br />Do you feel that sometimes you are just lost among the flood of opinionated statements from businessman, religious leaders and politicians? Do you feel disoriented when targeted messages and advertisements are bombarding you from all angles? Do you feel annoyed reading never-ending facebook debates with parties whose slogan surely is „Never really listen”?<br /><br />I do feel all these sometimes. And I think that I am not alone. It is because of the nature of the modern media, including the distracting social one and because we have limited time to uncover reliable sources of information. Occasionally we also have limited motivation to face the truth (instead of believing in convenient falsehoods).<br /><br />However, if we look around we can see that successful people are not behaving like that. They don’t believe in whatever is said to them. They don’t let themselves misled and deceived, not even by themselves. They seek out the necessary facts to make fruitful decisions, serving their own best interest, not that of others. They learn the effective methods to perform these tasks, essential for success.<br /><br />This book is about this truth-seeking process, describing its problems and difficulties, revealing the consequences of its failure and providing valuable advices to make it more effective. So this book is for those who has aims and who would like to maximize their chances to reach them.<br />The book contains a lot of chapters about various topics, each supported by relevant scientific research. You don’t have to follow all of the advices. As said above we all have limited time to read and learn. If you have an aim or passion you can focus on the relevant topics/chapters and learn only those bit of information which are critical to you. Take the title seriously and use the book as it is: a handbook of practical advices regarding modern age problems.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9213576527443490590" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


