<div id="review_3244394167" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3244394167" />
    <a title="Beatrice Sargin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/104956493-beatrice-sargin"><img alt="Beatrice Sargin" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3244394167?book_show_action=true">Mar 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beatrice Sargin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beatrice Sargin" href="/user/show/104956493-beatrice-sargin">Beatrice Sargin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3244394167" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17393815829504532022">The book, &quot;The Truth-Seeker&apos;s Handbook is amazing!<br/><br/>I have always been a lover of the truth, no matter what. The title of the book captured my attention to read its content and I have no regret. For me, there can only be one &quot;truth&quot; and it can be acquired through knowledge. Truth is wonderful. Learning about ways to achieve the truth and be a better version yourself is my goal. I definitely recommend this book.<br/><br/>If I had read this book earlier, I wouldn&apos;t have felt so much anger with my superior in </span>
  <span id="freeText17393815829504532022" style="display:none">The book, "The Truth-Seeker's Handbook is amazing!<br /><br />I have always been a lover of the truth, no matter what. The title of the book captured my attention to read its content and I have no regret. For me, there can only be one "truth" and it can be acquired through knowledge. Truth is wonderful. Learning about ways to achieve the truth and be a better version yourself is my goal. I definitely recommend this book.<br /><br />If I had read this book earlier, I wouldn't have felt so much anger with my superior in the company I previously worked with. I would have known that his behavior was a result of "confirmation bias". Hence, I would have acted differently and not being rude nor bitter with the way he handled work delegations. I would have been patient and learn to listen to him to accept changes. But since I knew his nature, I just wouldn't listen to him at all. I saw that he had no truth in him and can't teach me anything.<br /><br />In this book, I read about "Confirmation Bias". At the extreme, confirmation bias turns into wishful thinking. Our beliefs stem from what we want to believe, instead of what is true. Confirmation bias is a big part of the polarization in my opinion, especially in politics and among others.<br /><br />I am truly vulnerable to confirmation bias. To deal with it, I have to employ the flip-floppers strategy. It helps to practice mentally associating positive emotions such as pride and excitement, with the decision to change our minds and update our beliefs based on new evidence. I feel proud to be a flip-flopper!<br /><br />In addition to associating positive emotions with changing our minds, I have learned to use these habits to develop more accurate beliefs:<br />1) Deliberately seek out contradictory evidence to my opinion on a topic and praise myself after giving that evidence a fair consideration.<br />2) Consider the best possible form of arguments against my position and be open to consider someone's arguments.<br />3) Focus on updating my beliefs on controversial and emotional topics as these are harder for human mind to manage well.<br /><br />These ideas from the book will help me a lot as I intend to seek the truth always!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17393815829504532022" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


