<div id="review_3244233629" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3244233629" />
    <a title="Jo Anne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/111863732-jo-anne"><img alt="Jo Anne" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3244233629?book_show_action=true">Mar 23, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jo Anne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jo Anne" href="/user/show/111863732-jo-anne">Jo Anne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3244233629" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6590236508915128932">During this time, the issue of COVID-19 is a worldwide concern. The advice to stay at home to prevent the spread of the virus is a must. Hence, what better way to stay productive even at home is to learn something new? So I came across reading the book entitled, “The Truth Seeker’s Handbook: A Science Based Guide”. The title got me curious and as I look at the table of contents for the topics and it’s really interesting. <br/><br/>Sometimes, it’s odd that we are eager to know the truth but most of the tim</span>
  <span id="freeText6590236508915128932" style="display:none">During this time, the issue of COVID-19 is a worldwide concern. The advice to stay at home to prevent the spread of the virus is a must. Hence, what better way to stay productive even at home is to learn something new? So I came across reading the book entitled, “The Truth Seeker’s Handbook: A Science Based Guide”. The title got me curious and as I look at the table of contents for the topics and it’s really interesting. <br /><br />Sometimes, it’s odd that we are eager to know the truth but most of the time when it’s delivered to us we can’t handle it. When facing facts, we deal with negative emotions in which our minds are in denial and we go back to the things we believe in. I am guilty of this as most of the time my thinking is irrational when facing the hard truth. I am glad that this book focused on how we make decisions, on dealing our emotions and being rational. I am quoting the author on this, “Sticking to pre-existing beliefs that do not align with reality causes us to develop unrealistic expectations” and this has given me a new perspective on how I should deal with my emotions rationally. As what the author has said, “the emotional payoff is just one part you gain in orienting toward inconvenient truths instead of comfortable falsehoods”. By saying so, this will prevent us from making bad decisions which may have greater cost in our lives.<br /><br />This book has also identified different biases and presented strategies through real life experiences in which, as a reader, I can relate to. It speaks volume as it can be easily understood and reflect on your own if you have been suffering from any biases. I also love how the topics are presented like the first 2 sections of the book which focuses on individual aspects and how you can learn and grow and the last section talks more about leadership and the organization. I will definitely recommend this book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6590236508915128932" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


