<div id="review_2193565707" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2193565707" />
    <a title="Søren Ekelund" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/74170544-s-ren-ekelund"><img alt="Søren Ekelund" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1513522255p2/74170544.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2193565707?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Søren Ekelund" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Søren Ekelund" href="/user/show/74170544-s-ren-ekelund">Søren Ekelund</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2193565707" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18066667596063618669">The Truth Seekers Handbook is a collection of articles written and collected by Gleb Tsipursky.<br/><br/>It introduces the reader to the various biases modern people may suffer from, keeping them from accurately perceiving the truth, as well as the tools to overcome them.<br/><br/>The methods are based in science and well documented, and the author gives examples of use as well as anecdotes from his own experiences while explaining how they work.<br/><br/>Gleb also uses real world situations when pointing out the different b</span>
  <span id="freeText18066667596063618669" style="display:none">The Truth Seekers Handbook is a collection of articles written and collected by Gleb Tsipursky.<br /><br />It introduces the reader to the various biases modern people may suffer from, keeping them from accurately perceiving the truth, as well as the tools to overcome them.<br /><br />The methods are based in science and well documented, and the author gives examples of use as well as anecdotes from his own experiences while explaining how they work.<br /><br />Gleb also uses real world situations when pointing out the different biases and obstacles to truth in modern life, but commendably stays as neutral as humanely possible when it comes to the political scene.<br /><br />He ends the book with a “call to arms” against lies, alternate facts and fake news, in the form of the Pro-Truth Pledge, a grass root movement to further truth in politics, and keep politicians and public figures honest, something that strikes me as a useful, and seriously needed, measure in the current political climate.<br /><br />I found the book to be an interesting read, and though I pride myself on some insight in both the human psyche and fact seeking in general, I still found several new tools.<br /><br />I recommend reading the book from start to finish, and then use it as reference, when the need arises. This is an easy task, since the chapters are in article form and each deals with a separate term or tool.<br /><br />All in all I really recommend this book to anyone seeking a bit more clarity in their everyday lives, while navigating fellows, news and politics.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18066667596063618669" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


