<span id="freeTextContainer9805669879797131007">This is one of the books that I am excited to read until the last chapter because you would learn so many things. There are numerous strategies and techniques that one can apply to avoid potential disasters in decision making. <br/>I agreed with one of the statements in the book about Truth-seeking is a journey, not a destination. I am an introvert person. I usually follow my gut when deciding things for myself that led to dangerous errors. But, when I read the book, I&apos;ve learned that you need to hav</span>
  <span id="freeText9805669879797131007" style="display:none">This is one of the books that I am excited to read until the last chapter because you would learn so many things. There are numerous strategies and techniques that one can apply to avoid potential disasters in decision making. <br />I agreed with one of the statements in the book about Truth-seeking is a journey, not a destination. I am an introvert person. I usually follow my gut when deciding things for myself that led to dangerous errors. But, when I read the book, I've learned that you need to have research first instead of becoming impulsive, gut is helpful, but it can also lead us to a wrongful way.<br />One of the situations in the past that I made a wrong decision was when I applied for employment to a car company. I just applied because I saw their hiring post online and because the location was convenient to me. This without thinking what could be my future when I join the organization. I got hired but I only lasted for 3 months because of the poor people management and super toxic culture.<br />If I read this book back then, I should have done my thorough research about their profile, what benefits they have for their employees, and would not end up applying and wasting my time there. But I feel good reading this book as it serves as my guide in making decisions every day.<br />This book helps me every time I go out for shopping. Before, I just get what I want even if I don't need it as long as it looks beautiful in my eyes and ended up just using it once or twice. After reading this book, my behavior changes drastically when it comes to managing my finances. Now, I have an expense tracker. I also think many times and do my research if this product is worth buying. I’m still tempted to buy the latest products in the store but at the back of my mind I can hear - "Hey, get yourself a reward, buy that one, you only live once, so enjoy your money". However, I remember the 8-Step Decision-Making Model stated in this book that greatly help in avoiding serious problems.</span>
