<div id="review_3459390520" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3459390520" />
    <a title="Precious Quinte" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/115307412-precious-quinte"><img alt="Precious Quinte" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3459390520?book_show_action=true">Jul 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Precious Quinte" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Precious Quinte" href="/user/show/115307412-precious-quinte">Precious Quinte</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3459390520" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8469213237211056289">I am grateful to have read this book because it has given me enlightenment on how our decisions are greatly affected by people&apos;s opinions and suggestions on things. This book also has provided me with various strategies on how to be a good decision-maker.<br/><br/>I never thought that I could relate in this book especially in Chapter 9: Stop! Live the Life You Want. I could still remember how my godfather convinced me to enroll Accountancy as my college course because he told me that you will earn a lot a</span>
  <span id="freeText8469213237211056289" style="display:none">I am grateful to have read this book because it has given me enlightenment on how our decisions are greatly affected by people's opinions and suggestions on things. This book also has provided me with various strategies on how to be a good decision-maker.<br /><br />I never thought that I could relate in this book especially in Chapter 9: Stop! Live the Life You Want. I could still remember how my godfather convinced me to enroll Accountancy as my college course because he told me that you will earn a lot and you can easily land a job right after you graduate in college and all other good things you can think of relating to accountancy. Being so young ( a girl who was only 14 that finished high school and completely has no idea how the world works) and desperate to help my family right after graduation I believed him because I thought he knows better than I do and helping my family immediately is the only thing that I have on my mind at that moment. After taking the first semester of that course, I felt like I wasn't really happy, it doesn't excite me or sparked even a tiny interest in me.<br />I began to ask myself, is this course really for me? Do I see myself doing this kind of job until I get old? My heart and mind said no, that's when I realized that I have to shift or else I will be stuck with a course that was chosen based on my godfather's opinion.<br /><br />I was really surprised that there's a specific term to this kind situation, the mere- exposure effect where our brain has a tendency of believing that something is good and true just because it is somehow common for us.<br /><br />I learned about many types of biases especially the optimism bias which I really admit that I am a willing victim of this kind of bias. I always think that everything will go well and nothing can go wrong when I am deciding on things. But it turned out that I was completely wrong and too much of a good thing is not good anymore. Anything can happen, it may be good or bad that's why I am trying my best to address this bias with the help of this book. Had I read this book before, I might not be able to experience this kind of situation but still, I am grateful to have read this book especially in this time of the pandemic.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8469213237211056289" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


