<div id="review_2192843854" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2192843854" />
    <a title="Kenneth Whitaker Jr" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70517580-kenneth-whitaker-jr"><img alt="Kenneth Whitaker Jr" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577801148p2/70517580.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2192843854?book_show_action=true">Jan 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kenneth Whitaker Jr" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kenneth Whitaker Jr" href="/user/show/70517580-kenneth-whitaker-jr">Kenneth Whitaker Jr</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2192843854" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7311589688875035627"><strong>Truth and how to find it</strong><br/><br/>This book gives a lot of insight into how our brains work and helps us tell truth from untruth. It was very insightful in how to keep ourselves from falling into the pit of falsehoods that seems to surround us every day. It did seem a bit repetitive from time to time but otherwise a very helpful tool.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


